Package civitas.celestis.util.group

Class SafeArray<E>

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.util.group.SafeArray<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of element to hold
All Implemented Interfaces:
Collectable<E>, Listable<E>, Filterable<E>, ArrayGroup<E>, Group<E>, Transformable<E>, Serializable, Iterable<E>
public class SafeArray<E> extends Object implements ArrayGroup<E>, Iterable<E>, Serializable
A type-safe array of elements. This class is not thread-safe. An unmodifiable copy can be obtained by Group.copyOf(Group) to ensure thread safety, and effectively finalize this array's order and composition.

    • equals

      public boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj)
      Checks for equality between this array and the provided object obj.

      This will first check if the object is an array (either type-safe or primitive), then compare every element for equality with regard to their order.

      Tuples, Listable objects, and Lists will be also compared for equality by extracting their components and checking for equal composition and order.

      This equality check is broader than that of which is described in Group.equals(Object).

      Specified by:
      equals in interface Group<E>
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      obj - The object to compare to
      Returns:
      true if the object is considered equal to this array as described above
